        "title": "[codex] Add Codex reset credit menu",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Builds on #1638: #1638 added display for banked Codex reset credits; this PR adds the confirmed action to use one from CodexBar.\n- Adds Codex reset-credit consumption through the existing Codex OAuth account context, then refreshes usage after redemption.\n- Shows the Use Reset affordance in the menu/settings reset bank, including per-credit expiry detail and expiring-credit notifications.\n- Keeps reset-only credit snapshots in the menu-card usage/stacked-layout path so the reset bank still renders without primary/secondary windows.\n\nCloses #1502\n\n## Validation\n- `swift test --filter CodexResetCreditsMenuCardTests`\n- `swift test --filter CodexRateLimitResetCreditsTests`\n- `swift test --filter CodexResetCreditExpiryNotifierTests`\n- `swift test --filter CodexOAuthTests`\n- `make check`\n- `make test` attempted; shard 2 fails on `AlibabaCodingPlanCookieImporterTests.cookie import candidates honor provided browser order` because candidates are `[.safari]` instead of expected `[.firefox, .safari]`, outside this reset-credit diff.\n",
